co.cask.cdap.api.dataset.lib.partitioned

Class ConcurrentPartitionConsumer

  • java.lang.Object
    • co.cask.cdap.api.dataset.lib.partitioned.AbstractPartitionConsumer
      • co.cask.cdap.api.dataset.lib.partitioned.ConcurrentPartitionConsumer
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    PartitionConsumer

    public class ConcurrentPartitionConsumer
extends AbstractPartitionConsumer
    A PartitionConsumer that supports multiple instances consuming the same set of partitions by using a working set of partitions, and keeping track of their progress state during processing of those partitions.

      • doExpiry

        protected void doExpiry(ConsumerWorkingSet workingSet)
        Goes through all partitions. If any IN_PROGRESS partition is older than the configured timeout, reset its state to AVAILABLE, unless it has already been retried the configured number of times, in which case it is discarded.
